commit.message:
Fixup CI workflow

Fix #38

Restore 5.8 & 5.10 smokers
drop testing for 5.10 and 5.8. Something is broken upstream.
Use a macro for dealing with older SSL lacking macros
More structs opaqued in LibreSSL 3.5
Clarify croak message for missing passphrase
fix 'unsupported encryption' error on old library versions
support passphase protected private key load

Fix for Issue 31

Fix Issue 31 by removing reference to RSA_SSLV23_PADDING (removed from OpenSSL starting from v3.0.0)
Unify Makefile.PL to same style

Remove version check

We have defined 'use ExtUtils::MakeMaker 6.48;' where is minimal version
6.48. We could remove version checks.
Remove duplicit 'LICENSE' key
Bump changes to test workflow success
windows workflow fix
Bump to 0.32 for release to CPAN
Ensure that verify() leaves openssl error stack clean on failure
Figure out 5.14
Switch to github actions for testing
omit done_testing since it does not work for older perl versions
added test case for $SIG{__DIE__} handler

prevent outer $SIG{__DIE__} handler from being called

in case Crypt::OpenSSL::Bignum is not installed
Fixed broken SEE ALSO links.

Prefix internal bn2sv function so it doesn't collide with Net::SSLeay

Fixes https://github.com/toddr/Crypt-OpenSSL-RSA/issues/18

Revert 13df4d34e7cbc9d067f863ddb94260a26df3c9e6

This has caused significant regressions in other downstream modules and it has
always been possible to do $key->use_sha256_hash()
Update changes and version for 0.30 release
